## ğŸ›£ï¸ Routing System

### File-Based Routing

NextPy uses file-based routing just like Next.js:

```
pages/
â”œâ”€â”€ index.py              # â†’ /
â”œâ”€â”€ about.py              # â†’ /about
â”œâ”€â”€ contact.py            # â†’ /contact
â”œâ”€â”€ blog/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ index.py          # â†’ /blog
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ post.py          # â†’ /blog/post
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ [slug].py       # â†’ /blog/:slug
â”œâ”€â”€ users/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ [id].py         # â†’ /users/:id
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ [...all].py     # â†’ /users/*
â””â”€â”€ api/
    â”œâ”€â”€ hello.py         # â†’ /api/hello
    â””â”€â”€ users/
        â””â”€â”€ [id].py     # â†’ /api/users/:id
```

### Dynamic Routes

```python
# pages/blog/[slug].py
def BlogPost(props=None):
    slug = props.get("slug", "")
    return (
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Blog Post: {slug}</h1>
            <p>This is a dynamic blog post.</p>
        </div>
    )

def getServerSideProps(context):
    slug = context.get("params", {}).get("slug", "")
    return {
        "props": {"slug": slug}
    }

default = BlogPost
```

### Catch-All Routes

```python
# pages/docs/[...path].py
def Docs(props=None):
    path = props.get("path", [])
    return (
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Documentation</h1>
            <p>Path: {"/".join(path)}</p>
        </div>
    )

default = Docs
```

### API Routes

```python
# pages/api/hello.py
def get(request, params=None):
    return {"message": "Hello from NextPy API!"}

def post(request, params=None):
    data = await request.json()
    return {"received": data, "message": "Data received!"}

# Or use handler function
def handler(request, params=None):
    if request.method == "GET":
        return {"message": "Hello!"}
    elif request.method == "POST":
        return {"status": "success"}
```

